This paper is primarily focused on image retrieval using deep product quantization networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for generating adversarial examples, which is a topic of interest in computer security (cs.CR).
